Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Hickory smoked sausages{2} on another baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the wedges and sausages cook, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @sugar{1/2} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Once the onion is caramelised, divide the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} between the buns and spread it out evenly.

Add a sausage to each bun and top with your onions and a drizzle of @sriracha sauce{15%ml}.

Sprinkle over the grated cheese and transfer the loaded buns onto the baking tray used for the sausages.

Pop the baking tray into your oven until the cheese is melted and golden, ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into a small #bowl{}. Season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and add a pinch of @?sugar{1%pinch}. Mix together.

Add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl and toss to coat.

Pop your loaded sausages on each plate. Serve with the wedges and the dressed salad on the side. Enjoy!